text: St. Tammany Parish (French: Paroisse de Saint-Tammany) is a parish located in the U.S. state of Louisiana, in the New Orleans metropolitan area. The population was 264,570 in 2020, making it the fourth-most populous parish in Louisiana. The parish seat is Covington. The parish was founded in 1810. == References == == Other websites == * St. Tammany Parish government's website * St. Tammany school board's website Category:1810 establishments in the United States Category:1810s establishments in Louisiana
